Gauge theory: identification of the fields 
Every  supergravity background is
dual to a deformation of the four dimensional  SYM theory,
which has, besides the gauge field, two fermionic and two scalar
fields.


The two fermions,  and , can be identified looking
at their charges under the various symmetries; in particular they
have opposite chirality and different behavior under the
R-symmetry generators.

