The identification for scalar fields is quicker.

The SYM has two massless scalar degrees of freedom, encoded in the complex field ; its classical solutions give the two-dimensional moduli space of the theory. 

On the supergravity side, we have seen that the 
matrix is related to the motion of the branes in the transverse space; every static disposition of the branes in the transverse space correspond to a vacua of the four dimensional theory. After the twist branes are no longer free to move in the twisted , and every displacement in that directions correspond to an highly massive mode of field theory. Conversely displacements in the two untwisted dimensions
still have no energy cost and correspond to the massless scalars of the field theory,  to ; the freedom to choose the static position of branes finally gives rise to the moduli space of SYM. 

The motion in the untwisted  is parameterized by the sector
with  only of  , and the corresponding scalars are dual to the
chiral bilinear operators of  gauge theory. Thus the field
