In SYM there are no massless scalars and no moduli space, and indeed with the different twist  all the modes describing branes displacements  get masses.
In the supergravity background the field  can be still introduced, but there is no place for , as we have seen in the previous section.






The dual of such backgrounds with  turned on
are field theories with a massive deformation, deformation that can be seen as the remainder of the breaking of an original theory. 

We stress the fact that while in the case  and  correspond to operators which give vev or masses to massless fields, in the case the leading perturbation associated to  corresponds to adding mass to a field which is already very massive (as in).
