Gauge theory: identification of the fields The supergravity background for the KS model is not a regular  one. Nevertheless, since it is only a deformation of an  spacetime, we can guess that the  prescription that links the masses of the supergravity fields to their asymptotic UV behaviors and to the dimensions of the corresponding operators of field theory, still holds.
